{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":986,"text":"I'm a process engineer, I know all about\nboilers and incinerators"},{"time":5284,"text":"and fabric filters, and cyclones,\nand things like that."},{"time":8966,"text":"But I also have Marfan syndrome."},{"time":11022,"text":"This is an inherited disorder."},{"time":12921,"text":"And in 1992, I participated\nin a genetic study,"},{"time":17116,"text":"and found to my horror,\nas you can see from the slide,"},{"time":20574,"text":"that my ascending aorta\nwas not in the normal range,"},{"time":24375,"text":"the green line at the bottom."},{"time":25995,"text":"Everyone in here will be between 3.2-3.6,"},{"time":28902,"text":"and I was already up at 4.4."},{"time":31466,"text":"And as you can see,\nmy aorta dilated progressively,"},{"time":35676,"text":"and I got closer and closer to the point\nwhere surgery was going to be necessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40716,"text":"The surgery on offer was pretty gruesome."},{"time":43957,"text":"Anesthetize you, open your chest,"},{"time":46567,"text":"put you on an artificial\nheart and lung machine,"},{"time":49440,"text":"drop your body temperature\nto about 18 centigrade,"},{"time":52633,"text":"stop your heart, cut the aorta out,"},{"time":55321,"text":"replace it with a plastic valve\nand a plastic aorta."},{"time":59073,"text":"And most importantly, commit you\nto a lifetime of anticoagulation therapy."},{"time":64104,"text":"Normally, warfarin."},{"time":65956,"text":"The thought of the surgery\nwas not attractive."},{"time":68594,"text":"The thought of the warfarin\nwas really quite frightening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73035,"text":"So I said to myself,"},{"time":74325,"text":"\"I'm an engineer, I'm in R&amp;D,\nthis is just a plumbing problem.\""},{"time":77780,"text":"\"I can do this, I can change this.\""},{"time":79810,"text":"So I set out to change the entire\ntreatment for aortic dilation."},{"time":86659,"text":"The project aim is really quite simple."},{"time":90596,"text":"The only real problem\nwith the ascending aorta"},{"time":93521,"text":"in people with Marfan syndrome"},{"time":95106,"text":"is that it lacks some tensile strength."},{"time":97992,"text":"So, the possibility exists\nto simply externally wrap the pipe,"},{"time":103615,"text":"and it would remain stable\nand operate quite happily."},{"time":107173,"text":"If your high-pressure hose pipe\nor hydraulic line bulges a little,"},{"time":111868,"text":"you just wrap some tape around it,\nit really is that simple."},{"time":115392,"text":"In concept, though not in execution."},{"time":119238,"text":"The great advantage\nof an external support, for me,"},{"time":122352,"text":"was that I could retain\nall of my own bits,"},{"time":125065,"text":"all of my own endothelium and valves,"},{"time":127381,"text":"and not need any anticoagulation therapy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131741,"text":"So, where do we start?"},{"time":133047,"text":"This is a sagittal slice through me."},{"time":136051,"text":"In the middle, you can see\nthat little structure squeezing out,"},{"time":140593,"text":"that's the left ventricle,"},{"time":142104,"text":"pushing blood out\nthrough the aortic valve."},{"time":144949,"text":"You can see two of the leaflets\nof the aortic valve working there."},{"time":148140,"text":"Up into the ascending aorta."},{"time":150010,"text":"And it's that part, the ascending aorta,"},{"time":153988,"text":"which dilates and ultimately bursts,\nwhich of course is fatal."},{"time":159310,"text":"We started by organizing image acquisition"},{"time":162504,"text":"from magnetic resonance\nand CT imaging machines,"},{"time":167588,"text":"from which to make a model\nof the patient's aorta."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174021,"text":"This is a model of my aorta."},{"time":176244,"text":"I've got a real one in my pocket,"},{"time":178111,"text":"if anyone would like to look at it,\nand play with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180615,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":181648,"text":"You can see it's quite\na complex structure."},{"time":183737,"text":"It has a funny tri-lobal shape\nat the bottom,"},{"time":186306,"text":"which contains the aortic valve."},{"time":188325,"text":"It then comes back into a round form,"},{"time":190307,"text":"and then tapers and curves off."},{"time":193408,"text":"It's quite a difficult structure\nto produce."},{"time":197752,"text":"This is a sort of CAD model of me,"},{"time":199565,"text":"and this is one of the later CAD models."},{"time":201505,"text":"We went through an iterative process\nof producing better and better models."},{"time":205765,"text":"When we produced that model,"},{"time":208680,"text":"we turned it into a solid,\nplastic model, as you can see,"},{"time":212979,"text":"using a rapid prototyping technique,\nanother engineering technique."},{"time":217460,"text":"We then used that former"},{"time":218800,"text":"to manufacture a perfectly bespoke\nporous textile mesh,"},{"time":223471,"text":"which takes the shape of the former\nand perfectly fits the aorta."},{"time":227672,"text":"So this is absolutely personalized\nmedicine at its best, really."},{"time":231964,"text":"Every patient we do\nhas an absolutely bespoke implant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237497,"text":"Once you've made it,\nthe installation is quite easy."},{"time":240574,"text":"John Pepper, bless his heart,\nprofessor of cardiothoracic surgery."},{"time":245894,"text":"Never done it before in his life,\nhe put the first one in, didn't like it,"},{"time":249396,"text":"he put the second one in."},{"time":250787,"text":"Happy, away I went."},{"time":252085,"text":"Four and a half hours on the table,\nand everything was done."},{"time":254919,"text":"So the surgical implantation\nwas actually the easiest part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258745,"text":"If you compare our new treatment\nto the existing alternative,"},{"time":261957,"text":"the composite aortic root graft,"},{"time":263748,"text":"there are one or two startling comparisons"},{"time":266127,"text":"which I'm sure will be\nclear to all of you."},{"time":269475,"text":"Two hours to install one of our devices,"},{"time":271773,"text":"compared to 6 hours\nfor the existing treatment."},{"time":276184,"text":"As I said, the existing treatment\nrequires the heart-lung bypass machine,"},{"time":279689,"text":"and it requires a total body cooling."},{"time":281505,"text":"We don't need any of that.\nWe work on a beating heart."},{"time":284208,"text":"He opens you up,"},{"time":285523,"text":"he accesses the aorta\nwhile your heart is beating,"},{"time":287983,"text":"all at the right temperature."},{"time":289469,"text":"No breaking into your circulatory system."},{"time":291647,"text":"So it really is great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293160,"text":"But for me, absolutely the best point is,"},{"time":296523,"text":"there is no anticoagulation\ntherapy required."},{"time":299411,"text":"I don't take any drugs at all,"},{"time":301126,"text":"other than recreational ones\nthat I would choose to take."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303887,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305264,"text":"And in fact, if you speak to people\nwho are on long-term warfarin,"},{"time":308520,"text":"it is a serious compromise\nto your quality of life,"},{"time":311448,"text":"and even worse, it inevitably\nforeshortens your life."},{"time":315986,"text":"Likewise, if you have\nthe artificial valve option,"},{"time":318511,"text":"you're committed to antibiotic therapy"},{"time":320345,"text":"whenever you have\nany intrusive medical treatment,"},{"time":323436,"text":"even trips to the dentist\nrequire that you take antibiotics,"},{"time":326393,"text":"in case you get an internal\ninfection on the valve."},{"time":329252,"text":"Again, I don't have any of that,\nso I'm entirely free,"},{"time":332271,"text":"my artery is fixed."},{"time":334192,"text":"I haven't got to worry about it,\nwhich is a rebirth for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340226,"text":"Back to the theme of the presentation,\nmultidisciplinary research,"},{"time":343347,"text":"how on earth does a process engineer\nused to working with boilers"},{"time":346498,"text":"end up producing a medical device\nwhich transforms his own life?"},{"time":350499,"text":"Well, the answer to that is,\na multidisciplinary team."},{"time":353647,"text":"This is a list of the core team,"},{"time":356383,"text":"and you can see there aren't only two\nprincipal technical disciplines there,"},{"time":361630,"text":"medicine and engineering,"},{"time":362922,"text":"but also, there are various specialists\nfrom within those two disciplines."},{"time":367479,"text":"John Pepper was the cardiac surgeon\nwho did all the actual work on me."},{"time":372383,"text":"But everyone else had to contribute\none way or another."},{"time":375727,"text":"Raad Mohiaddin, a medical radiologist."},{"time":377561,"text":"We had to get good-quality images\nfrom which to make the CAD model."},{"time":381634,"text":"Warren Thornton, who still does\nall our CAD models for us,"},{"time":384481,"text":"had to write a bespoke piece of CAD code"},{"time":387489,"text":"to produce this model from this\nreally rather difficult input data set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394601,"text":"There are some barriers to this, though,\nthere are some problems."},{"time":397782,"text":"Jargon is a big one."},{"time":399059,"text":"I would think no one in this room\nunderstands the first four jargon points."},{"time":404645,"text":"The engineers amongst you will recognize\n\"rapid prototyping\" and \"CAD.\""},{"time":408115,"text":"The medics amongst you, if there are any,\nwill recognize the first two,"},{"time":411473,"text":"but there will be nobody else here\nthat understands all those four words."},{"time":415130,"text":"Taking the jargon out was very important"},{"time":417174,"text":"to ensure that everyone in the team\nunderstood exactly what was meant"},{"time":421355,"text":"when a particular phrase was used."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424029,"text":"Our disciplinary conventions\nwere funny as well."},{"time":426585,"text":"We took a lot of horizontal slice\nimages through me,"},{"time":429644,"text":"produced those slices and used them\nto build a CAD model."},{"time":433582,"text":"And the very first CAD model we made,"},{"time":435467,"text":"the surgeons were playing with it\nand couldn't quite figure it out."},{"time":440230,"text":"And then we realized that it was actually\na mirror image of the real aorta."},{"time":444119,"text":"And it was a mirror image\nbecause in the real world,"},{"time":447600,"text":"we always look down on plans,"},{"time":449435,"text":"plans of houses, or streets, or maps."},{"time":452008,"text":"In the medical world,\nthey look up at plans."},{"time":455189,"text":"So the horizontal images\nwere all in inversion."},{"time":458691,"text":"So, one needs to be careful\nwith disciplinary conventions."},{"time":461430,"text":"Everyone needs to understand\nwhat is assumed and what is not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466832,"text":"Institutional barriers were\nanother serious headache in the project."},{"time":470951,"text":"The Brompton Hospital was taken over"},{"time":473064,"text":"by the Imperial College\nSchool of Medicine."},{"time":475354,"text":"And there are some seriously bad\nrelationship problems"},{"time":479021,"text":"between the two organizations."},{"time":480502,"text":"I was working with the Imperial\nand the Brompton,"},{"time":482836,"text":"and this generated some serious\nproblems for the project."},{"time":485531,"text":"Really, problems that shouldn't exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488587,"text":"Research &amp; Ethics Committee."},{"time":490010,"text":"If you want to do anything new in surgery,"},{"time":492034,"text":"you have to get a license\nfrom your local Research &amp; Ethics."},{"time":495047,"text":"I'm sure it's the same in Poland."},{"time":496896,"text":"There will be some form of equivalent\nwhich licenses new types of surgery."},{"time":502348,"text":"We didn't only have the bureaucratic\nproblems associated with that,"},{"time":505515,"text":"we also had professional jealousies."},{"time":507626,"text":"There were people\non the Research &amp; Ethics committee"},{"time":510079,"text":"who really didn't want to see\nJohn Pepper succeed again."},{"time":512832,"text":"Because he is so successful."},{"time":514707,"text":"And they made extra problems for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518441,"text":"Bureaucratic problems."},{"time":520414,"text":"Ultimately, when you have a new treatment,"},{"time":523092,"text":"you have to have a guidance note\nfor all the hospitals in the country."},{"time":527133,"text":"In the UK, we have the National Institute\nand Clinical Excellence."},{"time":530777,"text":"You have an equivalent\nin Poland, no doubt."},{"time":532801,"text":"And we had to get past the NICE problem."},{"time":536110,"text":"We now have a great clinical\nguidance, out on the net."},{"time":538896,"text":"So any other hospitals interested\ncan come along, read the NICE report,"},{"time":543560,"text":"get in touch with us,\nand then get doing it themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548766,"text":"Funding barriers, another big area\nto be concerned with."},{"time":555164,"text":"A big problem with understanding\none of those perspectives."},{"time":557998,"text":"When we first approached one of the big,\ncharitable UK organizations"},{"time":562285,"text":"that fund this kind of stuff,"},{"time":563822,"text":"we essentially gave them\nan engineering proposal."},{"time":566251,"text":"They didn't understand it,\nthey were doctors, next to God,"},{"time":569071,"text":"it must be rubbish, they binned it."},{"time":570945,"text":"So in the end, I went after\nprivate investors, just gave up on it."},{"time":574205,"text":"Most R&amp;D is going to be\ninstitutionally funded,"},{"time":577459,"text":"by the Polish Academy of Sciences"},{"time":579843,"text":"or the Engineering and Physical Sciences\nResearch Council, or whatever."},{"time":583532,"text":"And you need to get past those people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585749,"text":"Jargon is a huge problem\nwhen you try to work across disciplines,"},{"time":588900,"text":"because in an engineering world,\nwe all understand CAD and RP."},{"time":592571,"text":"Not in the medical world."},{"time":594749,"text":"I suppose the funding bureaucrats\nultimately have to get their act together."},{"time":598345,"text":"They've really got to start\ntalking to each other,"},{"time":600721,"text":"and exercise a bit of imagination,\nif that's not too much to ask."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604101,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605336,"text":"Which it probably is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607249,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":608588,"text":"I've coined the phrase\n\"obstructive conservatism.\""},{"time":610972,"text":"So many people in the medical world\ndon't want to change."},{"time":614578,"text":"Particularly when some jumped-up engineer\nhas come along with the answer."},{"time":618118,"text":"They don't want to change."},{"time":619529,"text":"They simply want to do\nwhatever they've done before."},{"time":621982,"text":"And in fact, many surgeons\nin the UK are still waiting"},{"time":625305,"text":"for one of our patients\nto have some sort of an episode,"},{"time":628458,"text":"so that they could say,\n\"Told you that was no good.\""},{"time":631137,"text":"We've actually got 30 patients."},{"time":633397,"text":"At seven and a half years,"},{"time":635247,"text":"we've got 90 post-op\npatient years between us,"},{"time":637436,"text":"and we haven't had a single problem."},{"time":639236,"text":"And still, there are people\nin the UK saying,"},{"time":641398,"text":"\"That external aortic root,\nit will never work, you know.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":644527,"text":"It really is a problem."},{"time":646956,"text":"I'm sure everyone in this room\nhas come across arrogance"},{"time":649783,"text":"amongst medics, doctors,\nsurgeons, at some point."},{"time":653575,"text":"The middle point is simply the way\nthat the doctors protect themselves."},{"time":657963,"text":"\"Well, of course,\nI'm looking after my patient.\""},{"time":660338,"text":"I think it's not good, but that's my view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664739,"text":"Egos, of course, again a huge problem."},{"time":666862,"text":"If you work in a multidisciplinary team,"},{"time":668824,"text":"you've got to give your guys\nthe benefit of the doubt,"},{"time":671653,"text":"you've got to express support for them."},{"time":673553,"text":"Tom Treasure, professor\nof cardiothoracic surgery."},{"time":677043,"text":"Incredible guy."},{"time":678288,"text":"Dead easy to give him respect."},{"time":679802,"text":"Him giving me respect? Slightly different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682591,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684067,"text":"That's all the bad news."},{"time":685422,"text":"The good news is,\nthe benefits are stonkingly huge."},{"time":689667,"text":"Translate that one! I bet they can't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":693468,"text":"When you have a group of people\nwith different professional training,"},{"time":696731,"text":"a different professional experience,"},{"time":698656,"text":"they not only have a different\nknowledge base,"},{"time":700829,"text":"but also a different perspective\non everything."},{"time":703074,"text":"And if you can bring them together,"},{"time":704799,"text":"and get them talking\nand understanding each other,"},{"time":707635,"text":"the results can be spectacular."},{"time":710267,"text":"You can find really novel solutions\nthat have never been looked at before,"},{"time":715382,"text":"very quickly and easily."},{"time":717128,"text":"You can short-cut huge amounts of work"},{"time":720421,"text":"simply by using the extended\nknowledge base you have."},{"time":724050,"text":"And as a result,\nit's an entirely different use"},{"time":728846,"text":"of the technology\nand the knowledge around you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731908,"text":"The result of all this is that you can get\nincredibly quick progress"},{"time":736047,"text":"on incredibly small budgets."},{"time":738540,"text":"I'm so embarrassed at how cheap\nit was to get from my idea"},{"time":742437,"text":"to me being implanted"},{"time":743795,"text":"that I'm not prepared\nto tell you what it cost,"},{"time":746079,"text":"because I suspect there are\nabsolutely standard surgical treatments,"},{"time":750368,"text":"probably in the USA,"},{"time":751738,"text":"which cost more for a one-off patient"},{"time":756554,"text":"than the cost of us getting from\nmy dream to my reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761455,"text":"That's all I want to say,\nand I've got three minutes left."},{"time":764241,"text":"So, Ewa's going to like me."},{"time":766139,"text":"If you have any questions,\nplease come up and talk to me later on,"},{"time":769259,"text":"it would be a pleasure to speak with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771392,"text":"Many thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772424,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}